message.content:
cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new technique for radio resource management in cellular networks, which involves the sharing of spectrum between different generations of cellular networks. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the mutual effect of two different cellular networks and proposes a resource allocation algorithm based on the asymptotic signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) of the users. This involves the use of information theory concepts and techniques. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the problem of spectrum sharing in cellular networks, which is a key issue in communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system for spectrum refarming in cellular networks, which involves the use of an Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiple Access (OFDMA) system to refarm the spectrum of a Code Division Multiple Access (CDMA) system. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the uplink resource allocation problem of an OFDMA system, which is used for multimedia communication in cellular networks.
